                    "@type": "Question",
                    "name": "How do dividends work?",
                    "acceptedAnswer": {
                        "@type": "Answer",
                        "text": "A dividend happens when a company sends money (or, very rarely, stock) to its shareholders. When a company gets to the point that it consistently earns more than management can effectively reinvest in the business, establishing a dividend policy and sending those excess profits back to investors is a smart move.",
                        "author": {
                            "@type": "Organization",
