                },
                {
                    "@type": "Question",
                    "name": "What is dividend yield?",
                    "acceptedAnswer": {
                        "@type": "Answer",
                        "text": "Dividend yield is a stock&amp;#x27;s annual dividend payments to shareholders expressed as a percentage of the stock&amp;#x27;s current price. This number tells you what you can expect in future income from a stock based on the price you could buy it for today, assuming the dividend remains unchanged.",
