<section class="block-paragraph">
<h2 data-block-key="zc358">Dividend stocks are <i>long-term</i> investments</h2><p data-block-key="e4hrq">Even the most rock-solid dividend stocks can experience significant volatility over short periods. There are simply too many market forces that can move them up or down over days or weeks, many of which have nothing to do with the underlying business itself.</p><p data-block-key="fig7v">So while the companies listed above should make great long-term dividend investments, don&#x27;t worry too much about day-to-day price movements. Instead, focus on finding companies with excellent businesses, stable income streams, and (preferably) strong dividend track records. The long term will take care of itself.</p>
</section>
