<div class="qna-content">
<p data-block-key="cggm5">A <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/stock-market/types-of-stocks/dividend-stocks/how-dividends-work/">dividend</a> happens when a company sends money (or, very rarely, stock) to its shareholders. When a company gets to the point that it consistently earns more than management can effectively <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/stock-market/types-of-stocks/dividend-stocks/dividend-reinvestment/">reinvest</a> in the business, establishing a dividend policy and sending those excess profits back to investors is a smart move.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="qna">
<div class="flex items-center justify-between py-24 border-b border-gray-400 qna-header hub-faq">
<h3 data-block-key="rwodw">What are Dividend Aristocrats?</h3>
